The paper deals with game theory and algorithmic aspects of the Stable Marriage Problem, which are central topics in computer science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with combinatorial optimization and discrete mathematics, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
